54.4	Dian_Fossey	Dian Fossey	Dian Fossey (January 16, 1932â€“ December 27, 1985) was an American zoologist who undertook an extensive study of gorilla groups over a period of 18 years. She studied them daily in the mountain forests of Rwanda, initially encouraged to work there by famous anthropologist Louis Leakey. She was murdered in 1985; the case remains open.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b9/Dian_Fossey.jpg/220px-Dian_Fossey.jpg
